headline: Bridgewater reveals its top buys and sells of Q1 in latest filing
summary: A new filing from Ray Dalio's Bridgewater Associates shows the stocks the firm bought and sold during the first quarter. Among the top stocks bought are Alibaba (BABA), Baidu (BIDU), the SPDR Gold ETF (GLD), Palo Alto Networks (PANW), and Booking (BKNG). On the other side, the firm sold stakes in Alphabet (GOOG, GOOGL), Nvidia (NVDA), Meta Platforms (META), AppLovin (APP), and SPDR S&P 500 ETF (SPY). headline: Mark Zuckerberg Once Set Up A Facebook Account For Brooklyn Nine-Nine Star Andy Samberg, Then Personally Played Tech Support When Things Went A Bit Haywire
summary: In a 2014 appearance on The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon, comedian Andy Samberg revealed that Mark Zuckerberg not only persuaded him to join Facebook, now a subsidiary of Meta Platforms, Inc. (NASDAQ:META), but also personally set up his account and remained his only friend on the platform. What Happened: Samberg recalled the unusual story when Fallon asked if he was on Facebook. "Well, do we have time for a funny story?" he replied. "I am actually on Facebook, but I only have one friend.
